article.description: — Jacob Boonyasith's 17 points helped UMBC defeat Lehigh 88-62 on Saturday.
article.headline: Boonyasith's 17 points help UMBC beat Lehigh 88-62
article.linkText: Boonyasith's 17 points help UMBC beat Lehigh 88-62
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- — Jacob Boonyasith's 17 points helped UMBC defeat Lehigh 88-62 on Saturday. Boonyasith was 6-of-11 shooting (4 for 6 from distance) for the Retrievers (5-4). Yaw Obeng-Mensah scored 15 points and added nine rebounds. Colton Lawrence went 7 of 8 from the field to finish with 15 points. The Mountain Hawks (4-4) were led in scoring by Tyler Whitney-Sidney, who finished with 23 points and four steals. Evan Taylor added 15 points and six rebounds for Lehigh. In addition, Jake Betlow also had 15 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
